ehextractor - package ehextractor
Contains the analyzer and high-level classes responsible for extracting 32-bit exception handling information from programs compiled by the Microsoft Visual C++ compiler, finding functions, logging and checking if a binary can be handled by EHExtractor.
EHExtractor - Class in ehextractor
Highest-level class responsible for extracting MSVC exception handling information from a program.
EHExtractor(Program) - Constructor for class ehextractor.EHExtractor
Constructs an EHExtractor object for the given program.
EHExtractorAnalyzer - Class in ehextractor
An analyzer that extracts x86 MSVC exception handling information from programs and writes it to a log file.
EHExtractorAnalyzer() - Constructor for class ehextractor.EHExtractorAnalyzer
 
EHExtractorAnalyzer.LogLevelEnum - Enum Class in ehextractor
Enumerates the available minimum log levels to choose from.
EHExtractorScript - Class in Unnamed Package
Ghidra script to extract exception handling information from executables compiled with MSVC and targeted at 32-bit x86 architectures.
EHExtractorScript() - Constructor for class EHExtractorScript
 
EHHandler - Class in msvc.exceptions.code
Class for looking for exception handling setup code and extracting FuncInfo addresses.
EHHandler(Program) - Constructor for class msvc.exceptions.code.EHHandler
Initializes an EHHandler object for the given program.
equals(Object) - Method in class msvc.exceptions.Range
Compares this range with the specified object for equality.
extractEHSetupAddress(Function) - Method in class msvc.exceptions.code.Prologue
Attempts to extract the address where the code begins that registers a FuncInfo structure and that starts the main exception handler for the given function.
extractFuncInfoAddress(Address) - Method in class msvc.exceptions.code.EHHandler
